caption: Looking over the menu, expectations were high; now that I am sitting with some espresso after a complete meal (brunch with some appetizers and entrees), my expectations were far exceeded. The food, drink, etc was all so much better than I thought possible. Come here and try everything!
We just had Take out this evening and the food was marvelous.
Veal Cheeks....👍👍👍
Unpretentious and delicious. Authentically french, good service. Bravo.
Nice environment and very personal service. The menu was crisp and enchanting. Will absolutely recommend this restaurant to anyone. Convenient prices and big meals. Great job.
Service was very good. Everyone had a good  attitude. Food was very good but didn't seem to justify the high cost. My three companions agreed

Great food and service. They now have outdoor seating! I like that the restaurant is not in a busy part of Georgetown.  The food really takes me back to my visits to Paris.  The prices are reasonable for the neighborhood it's in.
Had a great experience in here with my girlfriend. The food came quickly and the service is just great. Prices are fair.

Really nicely executed classic French food in a comfortable setting. Salad was perfectly dressed, not overdone and same with the salmon tartare we had. Trout meuniere was perfectly cooked and the sauce was light but flavorful. Nice flaky piece of fish too. Had the Ile Flottante and chocolate cake for desert, which were also well done.

This restaurant is definitely one of the coolest place to eat in the region. Whenever I go there I am profoundly glad. They keep their high  standard service and the topmost level of dishes  they provide. You no doubt will love this restaurant. Highly  recommended.
Quaint bistrot, like being in Bordeaux!

My grandmother loves going here, and takes us every time we visit. The staff is super friendly and the food is really good! Highly recommend the steak- always a crowd favorite! We have reserved their event space for many family events and they are super accommodating and helpful every time.

We arrived at this restaurant for a meeting. we heard about this restaurant from many people.  Well, we were not disappointed. we were warmly welcomed by the crew  and we had a fantastic feeling. The food was just great. We had a great time and we will visit this place again. We recommend this place to all.

I love this spot! They prepare high quality dishes, they have a rich menu, The cook in that place is very experienced, I love a lot eating all their food. The dishes are consistently tasty, the service towards the guests  is nice. I  go often to this restaurant and I not even once was unhappy.  I highly recommend it.
Delicious food! Nice live music! Great wine and port choices.
Stumbled in on Christmas day. Hopefully, the quality of food was due to the kitchen being busy. The meal was overpriced perhaps due to the location.

This was an amazing restaurant with a wonderful selection of food.  I've eaten here a number of times and I've never had anything less than a spectacular meal here. While I'm certain there must be vegetarian options, there does seem to be a real push for veal here. Veal kidneys, veal cheeks, veal everything. It's all delicious and you should certainly go try these dishes without your judgemental friends.
Delightful is the best descriptive word I can think of. Lovely jazz on Mondays, scrumptious food and great service.

Very good French dishes from salads to main courses and desserts served in an intimate atmosphere. This restaurant is worth the trip, but you do have to drive through the usual Georgetown area traffic to get there.

Warm friendly service with rich French country food.  Excellent cassoulet for me. Liver for Herself. Chocolate torte to die for. All serious artery clogging food for a once a year treat. Convenient parking in the paint store lot across the street.
A mainstay French restaurant for classic French fair in Georgetown!
Great food, great service, and intimate vibe
Amazing food. The atmosphere is great. The staff is always friendly here.

We had eaten here several times -- as DC visitors -- during the past 15 years or so. This time, coincident with a restaurant week promotion. Service was unobtrusive and efficient. Good, warmed baguette. Wine list had lots of interesting bottles at what I thought were fair prices. The RR menu had many choices in the appetizer and main course categories. We were surprised by the high quality of sweetbread  and pied de porc appetizers. Mains were excellent, as were our ile flottante desserts. In Paris, this place would be a nice and  reasonably priced find.

Stopped in for restaurant week with a colleague and everything was perfect. I got the beef medallions and she got the trout. Both were mouth watering. The beef was maybe the most tender I’ve ever had.
I really enjoy their food. I always get excellent service there. The place is neat and the workers are always nice. Would recommend to others.
Wonderful food and great service!

I love this restaurant! They serve first-cleass meals, their menu is decent, The chef in that place is very experienced, I enjoy a lot tasting all their food. The dishes are always of high class, the service towards the guests  is nice. I  go often to this restaurant and I was never unsatisfied. I recommend it to all.
Live music, punctual service, cool digs,  beautiful food (eat the veal cheeks) - What more could you want?
(Translated by Google) Magnificent!  (Original) Magnifique!
Great food, nice wine bar upstairs.
Excellent
Food was delicious and service was on top. Grate place for romantic dinner
Savoury French fare, good wine (I got the one from Alsace), in a small, cozy town house setting in Georgetown.

Pricey, noisy.....Bread is good. I tried again...Still pricey, noisy and no improvement in the kitchen. My moules provençales......had nothing from a provençale receipe... Chef should be sent to France  to improve his skil lb s.

Nice wine tasting, great service, authentic bistrot type food in a lively atmosphere. We love our waiter who seemed to be the owner by the way he took care of us, great entertainer, we enjoyed ourselves the 2 hours we spent there. I recommend the Bistrot  Lepic.
Great food and helpful staff!
Lovely place, delicious food, great location !

WINE BY THE GLASS Bordeaux - $15 - really tangy and full-bodied Chinon - $12 - dry and medium-bodied Malbec - $12 - this was my favorite it was well rounded *found the wines by the glass list pretty basic  MOUSSE DE FOIE GRAS  - $14 Chicken and foie gras mousse terrine, apple compote *really enjoyed the terrine, was pleasantly surprised the apple compote complemented the richness perfectly, it would have been nice if there was a fresh element like mixed greens  JOUES DE VEAU BRAISEES - $32 Braised veal cheeks (osso-bucco style), served with fresh pasta and basil *veal cheeks were nice and tender, pasta was thick and held the sauce well.  The orecchiette tasted like box pasta (?) and not home made so when I see "fresh pasta" on the menu I'm expecting irregularly shaped ear pasta.  TARTE CHAUDE AU CHOCOLAT - $10 *definitely would not recommend this chocolate tarte, it was stale tasting and the chocolate was very dry *I ended up taking it home because I didn't want to waste $10 but I probably won't eat it ha *This should not have been served and removed from my check  SERVICE: -Minimal considering it was 5:30 pm when they opened and only 3 tables total when dining there for less than an hour. -Also I was irritated that specials were offered to the other 2 tables but not mine.  I heard Gazpacho soup, duck confit and another dish...after I ordered both my appetizer and entree.  Two thumbs down!
We were very impressed.  We want to come back for jazz night.
Great food and atmosphere.  Feels like I'm in Paris.
Amazing French food.  On par with anything I've had in New Orleans or Montreal. Great service too.  Great date night spot.
Magnificent meal and service. The quality is unparalleled and always consistent. Thank you for an amazing experience last night.
Worthy experience go back for more

Excellent wine list, food and service. The upstairs level is a nice laid back experience. Monday and Wednesday they have live music. Tuesdays they have wine tastings. Best to get a reservation. I will be returning.

Cool little french bistro with live music.  I can only share my thoughts on the wine bar upstairs.  There was a flamenco guitar player adding some atmosphere to the evening.  Bartender was very attentive and the wine selection seemed top notch.  The crowd was a bit older (looked like 50's - 60's) and everyone was hanging out and lounging.  Atmosphere was casual.  A pretty unique part of the D.C. bar scene and worth a visit.
Incredible. The wine bar upstairs is excellent 🍷
Visit Ted at the upstairs bar and he will take care of you.  Monday and Wednesday live French music
Food is epic! Those foodie types out there need to try....
Great food and friendly service. They are also very accommodating and will rent out the space upstairs for private events. Their passed hors d'oeuvres are also delicious.
Love it as always.  Was taken for my birthday.  Super busy but always excellent service and cuisine.
Can't say enough about this place. Just go...
Excellent French cuisine!
Great menu, selections well prepared, nice intimate room, staff is first rate. A step above the rest.
Good food.

This popular restaurant represents what Americans think is French cooking.  The menu consists of text book dishes that lack a certain authenticity but which cater to popular appeal.  Wrapped butter and Coquilles St Jacques not in a shell do not press my European buttons but there we are.  Enjoy but don't think you're in France because you are certainly not.  And very noisey.
Still one of our all time favorite date nights.
I had the smoked salmon.  It was absolutely delicious.  I cant wait to go back with my husband
Good french food
Braised veal cheeks with pasta were the best!
Intimate French bistrot in #Georgetown. Excellent food and drink and great staff!
Love this place.  Cozy and the food is fantastic
Great food and hidden gem in Georgetown.  The chicken in coconut curry is amazing!
Excellent food and wine. Great evening.

Fiancé' and I came here for Valentine's day. The restaurant is 2 floors, the bottom is the dining room and the top is a lounge area. The food here was excellent, cooked perfectly and served very nicely. The portions are fine overall, maybe a little less then other places, but they make up for it in the taste. The price can be a bit steep here when you add in drinks, so do tread cautiously. After dinner we went up to the lunge where they had a live musician playing jazz, which was very relaxing and nice right after our meal. Would recommend checking out this small spot in Northern Georgetown.
Add to your bar/dine-out list.

The atmosphere and food we're wonderful. I got the onion tart and my mom got the escargot for appetizers. The onion tart was phenomenal and the salad it came with was wonderfully dressed. My mom likes the escargot but felt that it was a little too heavy on the bread crumbs. I got the lamb shank special and my mother got the trout and both were phenomenal. For dessert we had the floating islands and it couldn't have been a better end to a great meal. The staff was attentive but we never felt rushed, our dishes came out in a timely fashion and we had a wonderful time. We will definitely be returning.

So this was a bit of a surprise. I'm not typically one to like French food, and this place doesn't look like much from outside. However... Wow!  The food was delicious, and the quantities we're generous (for French food). Meaning that you probably aren't walking out with a take home bag, but you aren't looking at a plate of design instead of substance.  But the food is designed, and cooked and prepped with care. You can tell the sauces are simmered and reduced, and the meats are fall off the bone.  Wine pairings recommended were great and not too expensive.  If I ever have guests who want to eat French, or if I just want good food, I'm making a trip here.  To put it easily... Filomena is to Italian what Bistro Lepic is to French.  Nice servers too!
Great cozy spot with intimate bar upstairs. The liver entree was cooked perfectly.

I reserved a table for two people, which should have been indicated to a manger or a server it was a date, but for whatever reason, we were seated next a party of more than ten people. We ended up yelling at each other. It was just horrible.
Great food and great atmosphere
Delicious, great service, lovely atmosphere and good value
Steak frites and eggs extrodinaire
Love the food and the service. Excellent wines.

A real find, classic French food, no foam or kale or other trendy stuff.  Just well prepared appropriately priced food with attentive helpful service. Wonderful reasonably priced wines.  They even have splits.  You can’t go wrong with calves liver, veal cheeks or lamb dishes.  Other reviews I’ve read rave about other dishes.  Desserts are insanely good.  On another there are always customers speaking French as it is near the French embassy.  Also appears in a number novels set in DC.  We’ve eaten there at least three times and will be back for more.
Awesome wine bar with reasonable prices, great atmosphere and most importantly, fabulous wine!
It feels like you are in France when you eat in this charming bistro. Food and service are always top notch.
Great wine list. Good food and good service. Live music is nice but a bit loud at times.
Authentic French restaurant,  good food and wine.  They also have a lounge with live jazz upstairs on certain evenings.
(Translated by Google) Fantastic !!!!!  (Original) Fantastique !!!!!
This is an authentic French restaurant.  Small place yet cozy. They have an upstair lounge with live jazz music.  Food is excellent. The owner is nice.
In DC for family memorial service - went here for lunch after service for a luncheon planned by a cousin. Amazing food and service! Wish I lived closer to return frequently!
A real friendly place to end the day
Good food and wine, nice and relaxed.
Always and reliably impeccable!
Absolutely charming small French restaurant. Quality cooking, and the lunch prefix menu is affordable!

Bistrot Lepic has fallen a long, long way from when it was a pretty good French restaurant on Wisconsin Avenue. Today, the place is ghastly overpriced for heavy, over-spiced and ill-prepared dishes.  Soft shell crabs - supposedly sautéed - covered in a caper sauce. Rather than crisp, the crabs were served soggy over a small scoop of spinach cooked sometime earlier in the day.  Pork served without imagination other than a scoop of mushrooms, mashed potatoes and sauce. Let's be honest ... the restaurant used to be a strong 4-stars, never 5.  Today, a single star is a gift.
Great food, pleasant staff where you can converse at normal volumes.
Excellent food and service. Pigs feet and escargot combination was recommended and the advice was on target. Great wine selection.  French food served in an eclectic way.
Cozy French Resturant with good food and Great local Jazz
A little bit of everything. Casual, romantic, relaxing, classy and above all delicious food. Highly recommended.

Simply great French food. Considering it's close to Georgetown, the prices are reasonable. For several glasses of wine, appetizer, entree and a shared dessert is was about $100 per person. I went for my anniversary and I would definitely go back. Several of the tables there where conversing in French which I always take as a good sign.
We have been there a number of times, as we used to live nearby. Cozy place, nice bistro food. A good place for a relaxed dinner, as it should be.
Small brunch event, with very good food!
Classic French dishes in traditional setting. Lively crowd and tight seating add to the experience.
Great food. Excellent service. Went back many times. Never disappointed!
Nice option for live music and relaxing ambience upstairs with more formal dining downstairs
Gave it 2 stars because the service was that bad. Food was great, but my God the service was horrible.
Classic French cuisine in a bistro atmosphere.

Excellent French bistro that is more on the provincial side. A bit on the pricier side, but worth the expense for special occasions. The only downside is that, being more provincial style, the desserts are a bit under what most would expect from French pastries.
Had a great overall lunch experience.
Great "cozy" atmosphere. Excellent French cuisine.
Foods good, though a bit over priced.
GREAT WINE SELECTION and the wait staff is extremely helpful, quick to offer a tasting.
Excellent service and food, snails, kidneys, duck, and pork belly...
Endive salad for appetizer and the Flounder for main were very good.
Nice staffs and wide varieties of wine beverages to choose from.

One of my favorites in DC. I hope you don't discover it so I can still get a seat at the hip little wine bar upstairs when I come in! Killer food, awesome staff, old school vibe, French country cooking - and one of the best bartenders in the city working the stick upstairs. Go say hi to Teddy! Owner is also an awesome guy, and is on the floor chatting with folks almost every time I've been there.
Incredible food and wine, every dish we had was amazing. Great, cozy, unpretentious atmosphere. Made for a really great date night.
A neighborhood gem! Very cozy - excellent for a romantic night out or for a family gathering. Knowledgeable servers. Food that always pleases. Outstanding value.
Fantastic romantic spot with great wine collection.
Comfortable, relaxed, able to have conversation, excellent food and service, easy parking.

Adorable little French restaurant. Good wine selection. We had the escargot as a starter, and it was my favorite part of the meal. For mains, I had the trout, and my date had quail risotto. Both were delicious and beautifully presented.
For me the best French restaurant in DC. Excellent products. Typical French dishes very well executed. Good wines also.

The food was ok; I have a very high standard for French food. The dining area is very cramped; we were seated against a wall with artwork on it and I kept bumping it. There was no leg room and it seemed like the people at the next table were right in top of us.
First dinner of summer restaurant week 2017- escargots, veal kidney, and salmon, with live music Service was top notch, even though it was a busy night, and food was delicious!
Excellent. Perfect night out, lovely service! Must have... DELICIOUS
Delicious food, lively atmosphere and reasonable prices.
Good wine and live jazz

I ate a quick dinner myself here a few weeks ago and was not disappointed.  The Salmon was fantastic, cooked perfectly and nicely crusted.  The bartender's take on the last word was also excellent and his secret was not leaving the chartreuse in the glass (which I usually find overpowering).  The service is always great and it is a solid spot.
Good but pretty unremarkable food for the price (bar an excellent Ile flottante); slow but friendly service.
Great Food
Authentic and delicious.
Fabulous and memorable food!  Wonderful ambiance.

Nice ambiance, very good attentive service. We split the onion tart which was very good, a little salty. We shared both the trout and risotto and quail entrees. While fresh they just lacked in depth of flavor, particularly the fish.  Good but a little pricy for the quality.
Nice intimate venue for jazz. Comfortable sound volumes even near the front.

The seating is cool but pretty uncomfortable if you have more than two people seated (no leg space under the table) and pretty uncomfortable to eat the big meals dripping with the delicious sauce because the tables are very low. Food was great, service was knowledgeable but a bit inattentive for the fact that it wasn't crowded, and the space was tight.
One of my fav French restaurant in town. The owners are very nice and the food is good. Traditional French food.
Cosy French brunch, good food, but get there early if you want croissant!
Have come here twice for special occasions, and had a great meal both times.
We love the wine bar.
Very delicious food with good service
The little wine bar upstairs is not just a hidden gem, it's a zen garden with great wine, food and conversation. One of the best spots in the entire city.
Good food and service!

Came in for the first time on Wednesday for jazz night and it was superb. The food was so pretty that I didn't want to eat it. The service was personal and friendly. Cozy setting great for a semi romantic evening or a chill night with friends.
Great French cuisine a with fantastic red wine selection.

We were with friends in Bistro Lepic on Saturday January 24, 2015 and the food and wine were excellent. However: It was Restaurant Week in DC: the Bistro was packed and the three courses of the menu were served with a speed that would make any fast food chain proud. Once you had finished your course, two seconds later your plate was removed even if others at the table were still eating. And a couple of minutes after  all of us had finished, the next course would be served. The whole dinner for the party of four lasted slightly more than an hour and we felt rushed through our wine and the whole menu so that the table could be used again. On a cold and busy winter day - like the day we went - you are exposed to a lot of cold air when you sit next to the door which is very displeasing. Next time we know in advance and order another table.  Yes, we will go there again and give it another try as the food was excellent. We hope that this speed-feeding-attitude was really caused by the extraordinary conditions of Restaurant Week in DC.

We had our annual reunion with our much loved cousin and niece last night. Excellent service at the bar, and also at table where we enjoyed our starters of pate, beet and brie terrine, and the soup of the day. Unfortunately, we had to pass up on our mains when a gas leak shut down the kitchen. The manager and staff reacted quickly and calmly, evacuating the restaurant in an orderly manner and summoning the FD. Their care for our safety reflected their care for our dining experience. We could not be more pleased, and will definitely return.
Pal mal. We tried the half priced wines at the wine bar during happy hour and found it enjoyable. The pleasant lounge atmosphere also promotes the wine.

(Translated by Google) Small French restaurant, with traditional French food of the soil (kind of hot goat salad, pâté in crust salad gherkins, liver of veal, escalope with the cream). Not recommended for lovers of expensive meats and potatoes. Excellent value for money, especially for the US capital! One tip however: if the chef is not there, do not go out of the map, do not ask for a "dish of the day". Upstairs, sofas, you have a drink or enjoy a meal with one or two jazzmen who come twice a week.  (Original) Petit restaurant français, avec de la nourriture française traditionnelle du terroir (genre salade de chèvre chaud, pâté en croute salade cornichons, foie de veau, escalope à la crème). Déconseillé aux amateurs de viandes coûteuses et de pommes de terre. Excellent rapport qualité/prix, surtout pour la capitale américaine ! Un conseil toutefois : si le chef n'est pas là, ne sortez pas de la carte, ne demandez pas un "plat du jour". A l'étage, des sofas, vous buvez un verre ou dégustez un plat avec un ou deux jazzmen qui viennent 2 fois par semaine.

Really Bistrot Lepic was an excellent venue for my grandmother's recent 90th birthday celebration.  The food was definitely some fo the best I've had in awhile.  I had the magnificent onion tart as an appetizer and I am trying to find a recipe for a similar one because it wowed me so much.  I also highly recommend the salmon tartare.The beef medallions were pleasantly tender and well seasoned.  The chocolate tart for dessert was a nice end.
Simply put, amazing!
Lovely, quiet neighborhood bistro.
Love it. Great neighborhood French restaurant. Particularly fond of the wine bar upstairs.
mostly good, but it has lost its past touch on all fronts. food is now just good, no longer great.
great food, but the service has the most attitude you'll find this side of paris.
Enjoyable meal.   Less a "bistro" it seemed to me than a decent French restaurant.  Service was excellent and the decor comfortable with a touch of elegance.

What is a surprise is the commitment to classic French cuisine, a la 1950's-bisque, escargot, kidneys, veal cheeks. Old style but not stodgy, done with exacting care and impeccable taste. No new ground broken here, but why kick when the Lobster Bisque tastes as fresh as on the boardwalk in Marseilles, the escargot balanced with a perfect parsley and garlic butter sauce, the Rockfish nicely seared on a bed of spinach. Polite, proper and delicious.
